From: dct-quantization project
Subject: [PATCH 03] Add EOQ (rANS) transparent decompression to GGUF model loader
Date: 2026-03-28

Modify the GGUF model loading pipeline so that tensors stored with
GGML_TYPE_EOQ are transparently decoded at load time.  After loading
completes, every tensor has been converted back to its original
quantization type (Q4_K, Q5_K, Q2_K, etc.) and the EOQ wrapper is
fully dissolved -- no runtime code path ever sees GGML_TYPE_EOQ.

Design overview
---------------

EOQ is a TRANSPORT-ONLY compression layer.  On disk, a GGUF file may
store tensor data as rANS-compressed byte streams tagged with type
GGML_TYPE_EOQ.  The per-tensor metadata required for decompression is
stored as GGUF key-value pairs using the namespace "eoq.tensor.<name>.*".

The loader intercepts EOQ tensors at two points:

  1. create_tensor() -- When the loader reads tensor metadata from the
     GGUF header, it detects GGML_TYPE_EOQ tensors and looks up the
     original type from "eoq.tensor.<name>.original_type".  It then
     creates the in-memory tensor with the ORIGINAL type and dimensions
     so that buffer allocation, graph construction, and every downstream
     consumer sees only standard GGML types.  The compressed on-disk
     size (smaller) differs from the in-memory size (full), and the
     loader tracks this mapping.

  2. load_all_data() -- When the loader copies tensor data from the
     file into memory, it detects that an EOQ tensor's on-disk size
     differs from the in-memory size.  It reads the compressed payload
     into a temporary buffer, reconstructs the eoq_tensor_header_t
     from GGUF KV metadata, calls eoq_decode_tensor() to decompress,
     and writes the decompressed data into the tensor's final buffer.

GGUF key-value namespace for EOQ metadata
------------------------------------------

For each tensor named "<T>" that is stored as GGML_TYPE_EOQ, the
converter writes these keys:

  eoq.tensor.<T>.original_type     (uint32)  Original GGML type enum value
  eoq.tensor.<T>.num_blocks        (uint32)  Number of quant blocks
  eoq.tensor.<T>.freq_table_size   (uint32)  rANS alphabet size
  eoq.tensor.<T>.precision_bits    (uint32)  rANS precision (typically 16)
  eoq.tensor.<T>.rans_block_size   (uint32)  Symbols per rANS block
  eoq.tensor.<T>.compressed_size   (uint32)  Compressed payload bytes
  eoq.tensor.<T>.uncompressed_size (uint32)  Uncompressed payload bytes

Dots in tensor names (e.g. "blk.0.attn_q.weight") are preserved as-is
in the key, because GGUF keys are arbitrary UTF-8 strings and the
"eoq.tensor." prefix is unambiguous.

The compressed tensor data region in the GGUF data blob has the layout
produced by eoq_encode_tensor():

  [freq_table: uint16_t * alphabet_size]
  [block_offsets: uint32_t * num_rans_blocks]
  [rANS compressed stream bytes]

This is read as an opaque byte blob by the loader, and passed directly
to eoq_decode_tensor() which knows the internal structure.

Integration with patches 01, 02, and 04
-----------------------------------------

  - Patch 01 (ggml.h): Defines GGML_TYPE_EOQ = 43 and GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_EOQ.
  - Patch 02 (ggml.c): Registers type_traits[GGML_TYPE_EOQ] with
    blck_size=1, type_size=1, is_quantized=false.
  - Patch 04 (CMakeLists.txt): Compiles eoq_rans_v2.c and links the
    EOQ code into the ggml library under the GGML_EOQ build option.
  - This patch (03): Hooks the loader to call eoq_decode_tensor() when
    it encounters GGML_TYPE_EOQ.

